---

<section class="w-full">
  <!-- Quote Section -->
  <div class="px-6 py-12 md:px-10 md:py-20">
    <p
      class="font-tomorrow font-semibold text-[20px] md:text-[28px] leading-[1.4] text-web5-dark max-w-[1000px]"
    >
      <em
        >A betrayal dressed as mass adoption — easy enough to use, easy enough
        to forget what was lost. Underneath the promises of decentralization, it
        was servers and permissions all over again.</em
      >
      <br />
      We don't need another chain. We need <span
        class="bg-web5-purple text-web5-yellow">clear labels</span
      >.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Comparison Table -->
  <div class="flex flex-col overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Headers Row -->
    <div class="flex font-tomorrow font-semibold text-white">
      <!-- WEB 5 / 2 Header -->
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex justify-center items-center py-16 md:py-20 px-6 md:px-10 bg-web5-blue"
      >
        <h2 class="text-h3 uppercase leading-none tracking-wider">WEB 5 / 2</h2>
      </div>
      <!-- WEB 5 / 3 Header -->
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex justify-center items-center py-16 md:py-20 px-6 md:px-10 border-l border-web5-beige bg-web5-red"
      >
        <h2 class="text-h3 uppercase leading-none tracking-wider">WEB 5 / 3</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Features Comparison Rows -->
    <!-- Row 1: Off-chain vs On-chain or equivalent -->
    <div class="flex border-b">
      <div class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10">
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Off-chain</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10 border-l border-web5-dark border-opacity-20"
      >
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >On-chain or equivalent</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Row 2: Sub-cent fees vs PoW anchored -->
    <div class="flex border-b">
      <div class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10">
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Sub-cent fees</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10 border-l border-web5-dark border-opacity-20"
      >
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Expensive</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Row 3: Server-grade speed vs Rent payable in bytes and time -->
    <div class="flex border-b">
      <div class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10">
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Server-grade speed</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10 border-l border-web5-dark border-opacity-20"
      >
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Rent payable in bytes and time</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Row 4: Censorable vs Censorship-resistant -->
    <div class="flex border-b">
      <div class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10">
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Censorable</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10 border-l border-web5-dark border-opacity-20"
      >
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Censorship-resistant</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Row 5: Auditable vs Finality -->
    <div class="flex border-b">
      <div class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10">
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Auditable</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10 border-l border-web5-dark border-opacity-20"
      >
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Immutable</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Row 6: Open-source vs Expensive -->
    <div class="flex border-b">
      <div class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10">
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >Open-source</span
        >
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex-1 flex items-center gap-3 md:gap-4 py-4 px-6 md:px-10 border-l border-web5-dark border-opacity-20"
      >
        <div class="w-4 h-4 bg-black shrink-0"></div>
        <span class="font-tomorrow text-sm md:text-base text-web5-dark"
          >PoW anchored</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div>
    <div class="flex flex-col border px-10 py-20 gap-8">
      <div class="text-subheader1 font-semibold">
        No bait-and-switch, no hidden relay, no “it’s decentralized enough.”
      </div>
      <div class="text-body flex flex-col">
        <span>Pick blue for the dopamine scroll— </span>
        <span
          >but the moment you mint your passport, your property, your savings,</span
        >
        <span
          >the screen shifts red, and the price of sovereignty becomes visible.
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
